node.text:
Justice, Accountability, Equality, Respect, Responsibility, Unity, Love, Peace, Forgiveness and Healing..... this is what Black Lives Matter stands for.❤️
.
Black Lives Matter DOES NOT condone violent protests and mayhem, such as looting businesses, setting cars/buildings on fire, endangering the lives of innocent people. 
This behavior is drowning the message, and dishonors the memory of #georgefloyd, whose own family is pleading for the violence to stop. 
We at #morikassoutherndelights are praying for Healing in our Land🙏🏿🙏🏿🙏🏿
“Do Not Return Evil for Evil” 1Peter 3:19.
.
#blackouttuesday #stoptheviolence #peace #love #georgefloyd🙏🏾🙏🏾🙏🏾🙏🏾🙏🏾🙏🏾🙏🏾🙏🏾🙏🏾🙏🏾🙏🏾🙏🏾🙏🏾

node.text:
For many Believers, today is the day of Pentecost, The day that the Holy Spirit descended upon Jesus’ disciples. It should be a joyous, celebratory day, but it’s not☹️
.
As I watch all the violent protests taking place across our country, it saddens me. Trust me, I feel the pain, I’m right there with you. However, protests of this nature are counterproductive. What good can come from burning down your community, buildings, small businesses, looting, and the like? .
The wheels of justice are in motion now, so pleeeaase take a step back, a deep breath and stop the mayhem so the healing process can begin. Please give justice a chance to work now! Take care and God bless🙏🏿❤️
.
#pentecost #stopthemayem #takeadeepbreath #healing

node.text:
My heart breaks every time I turn on the news and hear about the death of yet another African-American at the hands of those whose job it is to protect us. Being a person of color should not be a death sentence, and African-Americans should be afforded the same rights, respect and protection as everyone else. When will this senseless violence stop?
.
Sending prayers of healing to the family of #georgefloyd and all the other families who lost their loved ones due to #racialinjustice. #enoughisenough this has to stop.
